729809f-a.text:
Van Duzer Street, at the S.E. corner of William
Street, showing an old house and a one-story restaurant addition. The house appears on Beers's 1874 map; ownership is not indicated.
May 28, 1927
P. L. Sperr

729799f-a.text:
292 Van Duzer Street, at the S.W. corner of William Street (right), showing the home of the Democratic Club. The house was owned by Dr. W. C. Anderson in 1874; by Karl Kapff from 1898 to 1907, and by A. Sommers in 1917. Dates refer to
maps on which the owners' names appear.
May 25, 1235
P. L. Sperr
